    "It may be due to the complex nature of the data, the use of which still remains unclear in some areas.",
    "• The use of Desktop 3DOF and Cardboard devices has been decreasing.",
    "However, in fields such as Psychology and Medicine, they were used in situations where passivity is a key point (e.g., viewing relaxing videos to assist ICU patients or reducing anxiety through meditation).",
    "Generally, Desktop 6DOF HMDs were preferred (70.5%) as they offered wider interaction and a sense of immersion, as well as supporting larger applications and a quantity of sensors.",
    "Data could therefore be acquired in real-time, and professionals could monitor user activities within the virtual environment."
